Toys collected for "Toys For Tots"!

You're invited to bring an unwrapped gift for a boy or girl to place in the "Toys for Tots" collection box at Eddie's Attic, and settle in for a night of music from the TV host, best-selling author and singer-songwriter Robin Meade. Nashville-based supergroup "Sixwire" joins Meade as she follows up six previous sold-out Atlanta concerts.

The holiday-centric shows (7:30 & 9:30pm) will feature fan-favorite originals and powerful covers, as well as Meade's own holiday music after collaborating with Grammy-winning songwriter Liz Rose (Taylor Swift's "You Belong To Me" "Tim McGraw" "White Horse" "Teardrops on my Guitar" and Little Big Town's "Girl Crush").

"Sixwire" is as adept at songwriting as they are at nailing rock, southern rock & country. Though "Sixwire" members have toured/recorded with Faith Hill, Richard Marx, Vince Gill, Lee Greenwood and others, they're currently most recognized as the band from "Nashville", formerly on ABC and now on CMT.

As for her own musical chops, Meade collaborated with Lee Brice, Kenny Loggins & blues artist Keb' Mo' for her sophomore album "Count On Me" (2014) which reached #29. Her debut album "Brand New Day" featured work with Bo Bice (American Idol) & John Rich (Big & Rich) (2011) and reached #24. Robin most recently appeared on Sixwire's holiday EP, joining them for the song she cowrote (2015) "Guess Who's Coming to Town". Robin has belted the anthem to millions of NFL and Nascar Sprint Cup race fans since 2010. She's performed with Richard Marx, David Foster, Jim Brickman, and The Tenors among others. She earned a standing ovation on the Grand Ole Opry, and was the featured guest performer at the Venetian Las Vegas for a 2-week run with Australian pop stars Human Nature, after their holiday duet hit #16 (2014).

Fans know Robin best as the popular anchor of "Morning Express with Robin Meade" on HLN.

Broadcasting from the CNN Center since 2001, she's the longest running female anchor of a national morning TV news show. Among her assignments: jumping out of a perfectly good plane with President George HW Bush (2009), covering President Obama's inauguration (2013) and hosting "Ask Oprah's All Stars" at the mogul's request (2011). She provides newscasts for Cumulus' syndicated "America's Morning Show", is the face of HLN's "Salute to Troops" and hosts "Accent Health" with Dr Sanjay Gupta. Meade is in the Ohio Broadcaster's Hall of Fame, and is the recipient of the prestigious Gracie Award for Outstanding
